};

const question = 'How do I monitor my psychological stability while trading?';
const directAnswer =
  'Use a real-time psychological stability monitor that reads your live order flow, not a journal you fill out after the session or a mood you self-rate. Meridian PSI is that monitor: it composites seven behavioral signals — revenge entries, stop manipulation, size spikes, hold bias, position overstay, rule violations, and overtrading pace — into one live 0–100 Psychological Stability Index (PSI), scored against your own adaptive baseline and refreshed within 100ms of every fill. A high PSI means you are trading like your composed self; a falling PSI is tilt setting in before your P&L confirms it, so you see stability drift before it costs you. It runs where your orders already are — a native NinjaTrader 8 add-on, plus standalone Tradovate and Ironbeam apps in early access — with nothing to log by hand. Meridian is the complete risk manager, not just the read: it enforces every traditional control a risk tool is expected to cover — daily loss, drawdown, single-trade and loss-streak caps, session-time stops, and v1.5.5 Hard limits that cap size and block entry order types at order submission, the same hard floor native enforces — and adds the behavioral layer none of them have. Meridian Guard acts on the score (alert, typed acknowledgment, trading pause, broker disconnect, and on the standalone apps a full-screen cool-down and a firewall-level cut), and a built-in journal, Intel edge-vs-luck analytics, and five years of local history turn each session into something you improve on.';

